oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Osborne Brothers Publicity Photo
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Banjo; Grand Ole Opry (Radio program); Mandolin; Musical instruments; Osborne Brothers; Osborne, Bobby; Osborne, Sonny;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Four black and white photos related to the Osborne Brothers, members of WSM's Grand Ole Opry. The first photo is a half-length studio portrait of the Osborne Brothers with their instruments. The second photo features marquees outside of the Tahoe Harrah's announcing the Merle Haggard Show with special guest stars the Osborne Brothers. The third photo shows people sitting in lawn chairs watching the Osborne Brothers perform? The fourth photo is a head-and-shoulders portrait of the Osborne Brothers with a Country Music Association (CMA) Award. The photos were released by the Nashville Talent Service, Inc. A typed note on the back of the photo says, "January 1982."
